# u-forge.ai — LLM Rules Entrypoint

Routing guide and behavior constraints. Read this file first for every task.
Rule files in `.rulesdir/` cover specific topics — read only those that apply.

---

## Anti-Patterns — Read Before Writing Anything

These are active failure modes observed in this codebase. Violating them produces work that must be reverted.

### 1. Env vars are overrides, not requirements

`cargo run -p u-forge-ui-gpui` must work with **zero environment variables set**, degrading gracefully when no Lemonade Server is present. `LEMONADE_URL` exists only to override a non-standard location or port.

- Always try the sensible default first (`http://localhost:13305/api/v1`). `lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url()` implements this — follow it, never bypass it.
- Never call `env::var(...).unwrap()` or `.expect("set LEMONADE_URL")` at the top level. An unset env var must never be a hard error for core functionality.
- Tests: `cargo test -- --test-threads=1` must pass with zero env vars. Use `crate::test_helpers::lemonade_url().await` and silently skip — never fail — when no server is reachable.

### 2. Fetch live state before making capability decisions

Before assuming available models or hardware, fetch actual server state. `SystemInfo::fetch(url)` and `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover(url)` exist for exactly this reason — use them. Build a `ModelSelector` from the catalog to pick the best available model per capability. `AppView::do_init_lemonade()` (fetch → select → build providers → degrade gracefully) is the canonical example. Do not hardcode model IDs, device presence, or capability flags without a live catalog check.

### 3. Prescriptive plans belong in feature or bug files — not in shared docs

`.rules`, `.rulesdir/*.mdc`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and `README.md` must remain descriptive — they describe what **is**, not what **will be**. Implementation plans, step-by-step tasks, phased roadmaps, and `TODO:` sections belong only in `feature_*.md` or `bug_*.md` files.

### 4. GPUI: measure first, then apply known patterns

Before guessing at a UI slowdown, enable the perf overlay (`Ctrl+Shift+P`) and watch `frame:<ms>` while reproducing. `render()` call frequency is **not** frame cost — only the 1×1 timing canvas in `app_view/render.rs` captures it honestly.

→ **`.rulesdir/gpui-patterns.mdc`** — caching patterns, always-mounted panel, canvas coords, TextFieldView.

Key pitfall: calling `cx.notify()` from inside a `canvas` paint closure schedules a redraw and doubles work every frame. Size-affecting work belongs in `request_layout`, not `paint`.

### 5. Source code is the source of truth — docs are indexes, not mirrors

Every `.rs` file is thoroughly commented. `.md` and `.mdc` files tell you **where to look and why it matters** — not what the code already says. If you find yourself writing a struct definition or code example that already exists verbatim in source, replace it with a pointer (`see src/lemonade/rerank.rs — LemonadeRerankProvider`).

---

## Task-Based Routing

### Building, running, or setting up the environment
→ **`.rulesdir/environment-config.mdc`**
→ **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`**

`env.sh` is optional — no longer required for compilation. `cargo build` and `cargo test` work with no env vars.

### Writing or modifying Rust source (`crates/**/*.rs`)
→ **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`**

Error handling (`anyhow`), `EmbeddingProvider` trait (do NOT bypass it), `TranscriptionProvider` trait, `InferenceQueue` usage, `ObjectBuilder`, async anti-patterns, storage patterns.

### Adding or wiring a new AI capability (embedding, reranking, TTS, STT, LLM)
→ **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`** (trait sections)
→ **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`** (provider addition workflow)

Implement the relevant trait. Build via `ProviderFactory`, register with `InferenceQueueBuilder::with_provider`. Do NOT call provider HTTP clients directly from business logic. There is no `DeviceWorker` trait — that abstraction was removed in the hardware refactor.

### Writing, running, or debugging tests
→ **`.rulesdir/testing-debugging.mdc`**
→ **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`** (testing patterns section)

Every test gets its own `TempDir`. Mock providers for unit tests; `lemonade_url().await` skip-guard for integration tests.

### Schema files (`defaults/schemas/*.schema.json`)
→ **`.rulesdir/schema-system.mdc`**
→ **`.rulesdir/json-data-formats.mdc`**

### Data files (`defaults/data/*.jsonl`) or the import pipeline
→ **`.rulesdir/json-data-formats.mdc`**

### UI work (`crates/u-forge-ui-gpui/`, `crates/u-forge-graph-view/`, `crates/u-forge-ui-traits/`)
→ **`.rulesdir/project-structure.mdc`** (integration points, cross-cutting constraints)
→ **`.rulesdir/gpui-patterns.mdc`** (caching, panel patterns, canvas coords, TextFieldView)
